<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="576" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851D.01/4: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-08T17:00:00+01:00">September 8, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received September 8—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3039. The substance of your 2628, September 5, 8 p.m., has been
                                communicated orally to Admiral Muselier who appreciates the
                                information given. He had withheld his telegram pending receipt of
                                your views and says that he will not send it and will hold his hand
                                until he believes that Martinique, Guadeloupe, and French Guiana can
                                be “converted” simultaneously. He reiterated his desire to do
                                nothing to which we would object.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>